---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../styles/components/home.css';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Channel 47 and these Claude Code tools."
>
  <div class="home-section">
    <div style="max-width: 42rem;">
      <h1 style="
        font-size: var(--text-4xl);
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: var(--leading-tight);
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
      ">
        About Channel 47
      </h1>

      <div style="
        font-size: var(--text-lg);
        color: var(--color-text-muted);
        line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
      ">
        <h2 style="
          font-size: var(--text-2xl);
          font-weight: 600;
          margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
          color: var(--color-text);
        ">
          What This Is
        </h2>

        <p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">
          I built these Claude Code tools for my own work. Some I created from scratch. Others I found and tested extensively. Everything here is open source and free.
        </p>

        <h2 style="
          font-size: var(--text-2xl);
          font-weight: 600;
          margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
          margin-top: var(--space-8);
          color: var(--color-text);
        ">
          What You'll Find
        </h2>

        <p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">
          The plugins section lists tools I use daily. Each one solves a specific problem. If it's listed, I've vetted it.
        </p>

        <p>
          The blog covers workflows and patterns. I also write about how these tools work internally.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
